@startuml
[*] --> "Inventory is empty"
note right: Initial state
Inventory is empty --> Add Goods : User adds new goods
Add Goods --> Update Price : User updates price of existing items
Update Price --> Remove Expired Goods : System identifies expired goods and notifies user
Remove Expired Goods --> Place Order : User places order to supplier for additional goods
Place Order --> Generate Invoice : System generates invoice for the order once it is placed
Generate Invoice --> Search Items : User searches for items available in inventory and selects them for purchase
Search Items --> Calculate Discount and Tax : System calculates applicable discount and tax based on selected items
Calculate Discount and Tax --> Generate Receipt : System generates receipt for customer after purchase
Generate Receipt --> Replace Item or Cancel Receipt : User can replace item or cancel receipt during billing process if needed
Replace Item or Cancel Receipt --> Record Customer Request : System records customer requests for items that may not be currently available
Record Customer Request --> View Summary Report : User views summary report of all transactions carried out in system at any point
View Summary Report --> Inventory is empty : Final state

@enduml
